<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-20T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-20T04:00:00-05:00" n="518" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">761.6211/312: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-20T12:00:00+03:00">December
                                    20, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 20—11:18
                                a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1113. The press announces today without comment the arrival in Moscow
                            yesterday of Ritter, the German Plenipotentiary for Economic Matters,
                            and Schnurre, accompanied by an economic delegation including
                            representatives of the German Ministries of National Economy,
                            Agriculture, Foreign Affairs, and a number of experts.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>